 You're an adult and you don't even write kanji!

10
00:02:01,835 --> 00:02:03,400
 You're going to quit, senpai?

11
00:02:03,400 --> 00:02:05,400
 Are you going to go out with me?

12
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:06,397
 No way.

13
00:02:06,422 --> 00:02:10,210
 I'll write the reason in detail.

14
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:15,400
 Reason?

15
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:19,849
 The reason for the Tameyari Fireworks Festival?

16
00:02:21,400 --> 00:02:25,375
 I've never seen a firework festival since I was a kid.

17
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:27,400
 Idiot!

18
00:02:28,100 --> 00:02:32,100
 Do you know what kind of job you're doing?

19
00:02:32,100 --> 00:02:34,100
 Of course! I'm a police officer!

20
00:02:34,100 --> 00:02:40,100
 Do you think it's okay for a police officer to take a vacation at a firework festival?

21
00:02:40,100 --> 00:02:43,100
 The firework festival is held every year by amazing people.

22
00:02:43,100 --> 00:02:46,100
 I want to borrow a cat's hand as a guard.

23
00:02:48,100 --> 00:02:51,100
 It can't be helped. I'll pay for it.

24
00:02:51,100 --> 00:02:54,100
 If you do that, you'll be fired right away!

25
00:02:54,100 --> 00:02:57,100
 It's a joke! It's a joke!

26
00:03:02,100 --> 00:03:07,100
 The head of the department store is using the firework festival every day.

27
00:03:09,100 --> 00:03:13,100
 It would be great if I rode him and saw the fireworks.

28
00:03:13,100 --> 00:03:15,100
 Damn!

29
00:03:15,100 --> 00:03:17,100
 There's no way I can rest well.

30
00:03:18,100 --> 00:03:20,100
 Hey, Ryo!

31
00:03:20,100 --> 00:03:21,100
 Yes?

32
00:03:21,100 --> 00:03:22,100
 Hey!

33
00:03:22,100 --> 00:03:23,100
 What?

34
00:03:23,100 --> 00:03:24,100
 What?

35
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:28,522
 I just thought I'd pay you back.

36
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:35,800
 I can't pay you back.

37
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:46,800
 Is it that expensive?

38
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:47,800
 Yes.

39
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:51,800
 If Ryo pays me back, I'll have to pay for the firework festival.

40
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:54,500
 This is a step ahead of us.

41
00:03:54,500 --> 00:03:56,500
 There are big apartments all over the place.

42
00:03:56,500 --> 00:03:59,500
 Aren't there more people eating ramen?

43
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:03,500
 In a high-rise apartment, you can't even hear the sound of the firework festival.

44
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:05,500
 You should pay me back.

45
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:07,500
 I have a cell phone.

46
00:04:07,500 --> 00:04:09,500
 No, I can't.

47
00:04:09,500 --> 00:04:11,500
 I'm alone.

48
00:04:11,500 --> 00:04:14,500
 I can't ride the elevator while pulling the bar.

49
00:04:14,500 --> 00:04:18,500
 It takes too much money to pay with a helicopter.

50
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:21,200
