85
00:06:30,700 --> 00:06:32,700
 Calm down.

86
00:06:34,700 --> 00:06:36,700
 It's flying.

87
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:39,400
 You're a pro.

88
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:44,400
 The basic movement of the hot air balloon is adjusted with this burner.

89
00:06:44,400 --> 00:06:47,400
 It can fly high.

90
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:49,400
 It doesn't have to fly that high.

91
00:06:49,400 --> 00:06:51,400
 It can fly as high as a high-rise apartment.

92
00:06:51,400 --> 00:06:52,400
 What?

93
00:06:52,400 --> 00:06:54,400
 What?

94
00:06:55,400 --> 00:06:59,400
 It can also release the heat when it is fast.

95
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:01,400
 Releasing the heat?

96
00:07:01,400 --> 00:07:03,400
 You're enthusiastic.

97
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:04,400
 What?

98
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:06,400
 It's a business.

99
00:07:06,424 --> 00:07:07,075
 Business?

100
00:07:07,100 --> 00:07:09,100
 No.

101
00:07:09,100 --> 00:07:11,100
 I want to be a professional in the hot air balloon.

102
00:07:11,100 --> 00:07:17,237
 I want to do business flying in the sky in elementary school.

103
00:07:17,262 --> 00:07:18,278
 That's what you wrote, right?

104
00:07:19,332 --> 00:07:20,371
 Yes.

105
00:07:21,098 --> 00:07:22,260
 I'm counting on you.

106
00:07:23,004 --> 00:07:24,552
 I'll help you.

107
00:07:24,716 --> 00:07:26,100
